        <h2>1. JobNimbus — Best for insurance roofing</h2>
        <p><strong>Pricing:</strong> ~$200/mo for small teams; custom for larger (contact sales)</p>

        <p>JobNimbus was purpose-built for the roofing industry, particularly insurance restoration work. The workflow is designed around the insurance claim cycle: lead comes in, adjuster inspection, supplement negotiation, job scheduling, material delivery, and final invoice. Each stage has its own workflow board.</p>

        <p><strong>Roofing-specific strengths:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Insurance workflow boards:</strong> Kanban-style pipeline tracking from lead to paid</li>
          <li><strong>EagleView integration:</strong> Pull aerial measurements directly into estimates</li>
          <li><strong>Supplement tracking:</strong> Document and track insurance supplement requests</li>
          <li><strong>Mobile photo capture:</strong> Field reps can document damage and attach to the job</li>
          <li><strong>Sales rep management:</strong> Assign and track leads across your storm chasing team</li>
          <li><strong>Automated follow-ups:</strong> Email/text automation for lead nurturing</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Limitations:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Less suitable for commercial roofing or large-scale projects</li>
          <li>Pricing can escalate with add-ons</li>
          <li>Scheduling tools are simpler than dedicated PM platforms</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. AccuLynx — Best for growing roofing companies</h2>
        <p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Custom (contact sales; typically $250–$400+/mo)</p>

        <p>AccuLynx is a roofing-specific platform with deeper operational features than JobNimbus — particularly around material ordering and production management. If you're running 15+ jobs per week across multiple crews, AccuLynx's production tracking capabilities become valuable.</p>

        <p><strong>Roofing-specific strengths:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>EagleView and Hover aerial measurement integration</li>
          <li>Direct material ordering to suppliers from the platform</li>
          <li>Production board for tracking active installations</li>
          <li>Subcontractor management and payments</li>
          <li>QuickBooks integration for job-level accounting</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Limitations:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Custom pricing with no transparent tiers — requires a demo</li>
          <li>Implementation takes time; not instant setup</li>
          <li>Primarily retail and insurance roofing, less suited to commercial</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Jobber — Best for small roofing operations</h2>
        <p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Core $69/mo · Connect $169/mo · Grow $349/mo</p>

        <p>Jobber is a general field service management tool, not roofing-specific, but it's excellent for small roofing companies doing 5–20 jobs per week. Quote requests, scheduling, crew dispatch, and invoicing are all clean and fast. If you're not doing heavy insurance work, you may not need a roofing-specific platform.</p>

        <p><strong>Strengths for roofers:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Fast quote creation with line items and photos</li>
          <li>Online booking and quote request portal</li>
          <li>Crew scheduling and GPS tracking</li>
          <li>Automated payment reminders and online payments</li>
          <li>Client follow-up campaigns (review requests, etc.)</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Limitations:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>No roofing-specific workflows or insurance integration</li>
          <li>Not suitable for complex multi-phase projects</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Buildertrend — Best for roofers doing larger projects</h2>
        <p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Essential $499/mo · Advanced $799/mo · Complete $1,099/mo</p>

        <p>Buildertrend isn't roofing-specific, but if you're a roofing company that also does additions, gut rehabs, or large commercial roofing projects, it provides a PM depth that roofing-specific tools don't match. The client portal, change order management, and sub coordination tools are best-in-class for larger jobs.</p>

