        <h2>5. Contractor Foreman — Best budget option</h2>
        <p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Basic $49/mo · Standard $79/mo · Pro $159/mo · Unlimited $299/mo</p>

        <p>For roofing companies watching overhead, Contractor Foreman delivers more features per dollar than almost anything else. Estimating, scheduling, time tracking, and job costing are all included at $49–$79/month. It's not as polished as JobNimbus or AccuLynx, but if the price of those platforms is a barrier, this is a credible alternative.</p>

        <h2>Aerial measurement tools (separate from software)</h2>
        <p>Many of the best roofing estimating tools integrate with aerial measurement services — worth knowing even if you use separate software:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>EagleView:</strong> Industry standard. Generates accurate roof measurements from aerial imagery. ~$40–$120 per report depending on detail level.</li>
          <li><strong>Hover:</strong> Homeowner photos (or your own) generate 3D models and measurements. More affordable than EagleView for many jobs.</li>
          <li><strong>GAF QuickMeasure:</strong> Powered by EagleView, available through GAF distributor relationships.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to choose roofing software</h2>

        <h3>Insurance restoration vs. retail roofing</h3>
        <p>If more than half your work is insurance claims, you want a platform with insurance workflow tools — JobNimbus or AccuLynx. If you're doing mostly retail replacement and new construction, Jobber or Contractor Foreman may be simpler and more affordable.</p>

        <h3>How many jobs per week do you run?</h3>
        <p>1–5 jobs/week: Jobber or Contractor Foreman. 5–20 jobs/week with an insurance focus: JobNimbus. 20+ jobs with crew management needs: AccuLynx or a custom setup.</p>

        <h3>Do you need aerial measurement integration?</h3>
        <p>If you're estimating 10+ roofs per week, paying for EagleView reports individually adds up. Platforms with built-in measurement integration save both cost and time. JobNimbus and AccuLynx both offer this natively.</p>

